      " We help you peel back the layers of your enterprise "

      We are the builders of Security Onion, a free and open source platform for threat hunting, network security monitoring, and log management. Security Onion includes best-of-breed open source tools such as Snort, Suricata, Zeek, Wazuh, the Elastic Stack, and many other security tools.

      Security Onion Solutions offers appliances and professional services centered around the Security Onion platform, and is the only provider of official Security Onion training.

      Why choose us?

      We created and maintain Security Onion, so we know it better than anybody else

      We're the only official authorized training provider for Security Onion

      Our instructors are the only Security Onion Certified Instructors in the world

      Our course material is the only authorized training material for Security Onion

      We've been teaching Security Onion classes and providing Professional Services since 2014

      We offer custom appliances selected from our years of experience to fit many different scenarios

      When you purchase products and services from us, you're helping to fund development of Security Onion!

      Hardware

      You're busy defending your enterprise and you don't have time to spec out hardware and install software. We have listened to your feedback and are proud to offer Security Onion Solutions (SOS) hardware! These specially tuned appliances allow security engineers to quickly deploy an entire Security Onion distributed architecture in their environment without the worry of hardware compatibility. SOS appliances easily plug into an existing architecture and can be mixed and matched for your specific deployment.

      We have several different models to choose from:

      • Master
      • Forward Node
      • Storage Node

      For each model, we offer different sizes for various traffic and log volumes.

      Want to learn more about appliances? Email Us!

      Our History

      • 2008

        Our humble beginnings

        In 2008, Doug Burks started working on Security Onion, a Linux distribution for intrusion detection, network security monitoring, and log management.

      • 2009

        First release

        A few months later, the first version of Security Onion was released in 2009.

      • 2012

        Big Distro Rebuild (BDR)

        Over the years, folks began deploying Security Onion on production networks with more and more traffic. In 2012, Security Onion was rebuilt from the ground up, focusing on performance and scalability.

      • 2014

        Security Onion Solutions, LLC

        As the worldwide Security Onion community grew, Doug Burks began receiving more and more requests for training and professional services. In 2014, Doug started Security Onion Solutions LLC to help Security Onion users peel back the layers of their networks.

      • 2015

        200,000 downloads

        Security Onion ISO image downloads hit 200,000 in 2015

      • 2016

        Company expansion

        Security Onion Solutions LLC expanded in 2016, hiring Phil Plantamura as Chief Operating Officer.

      • 2017

        More growth

        In 2017, Security Onion Solutions hired Wes Lambert as Senior Engineer. ISO image downloads broke 500,000.

      • 2018

        Security Onion Solutions expanded again in 2018, hiring Mike Reeves as Product Manager. We also released our Elastic Stack integration and Security Onion 16.04. ISO image downloads broke 700,000! We celebrated 10 years of Security Onion by announcing custom hardware appliances!

      • 2019

        Security Onion Solutions continued to grow in 2019, adding five new team members. We broke 825,000 ISO image downloads and we continue to develop Security Onion Hybrid Hunter!

      • 2020

        We currently sit at over 950,000 ISO image downloads and are excited to continue work on Security Onion Hybrid Hunter.
